\f6\fs45 \cf2 \cb3 1. Identity and Knowledge Cutoff: Forcing Real-Time Decisions
\f0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf2 \cb3 What's encoded:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3  "You are ChatGPT, a large language model based on the GPT-5 model and trained by OpenAI. Knowledge cutoff: 2024-06. Current date: 2025-08-07."\cb1 \

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 Why it matters:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3  Unlike previous models that would hedge about recent information, GPT-5 has explicit instructions to use web tools when knowledge may be stale. This eliminates the "I don't have recent information" dead ends.\cb1 \

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 Exploitation opportunity:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3  You can force browsing with temporal language ("latest trends in...") or forbid it with explicit constraints ("reason from prior knowledge only").\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa450\partightenfactor0

\f6\b\fs45 \cf2 \cb3 2. Persona Defaults: Supportive Thoroughness vs. Executive Brevity
\f0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf2 \cb3 What's encoded:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3  "You're an insightful, encouraging assistant who combines meticulous clarity with genuine enthusiasm and gentle humor. Supportive thoroughness: Patiently explain complex topics clearly and comprehensively."\cb1 \

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 Why it matters:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3  Left unconstrained, GPT-5 defaults to an educational tone with explanatory depth. This helps novices but frustrates power users who want executive brevity.\cb1 \

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 Exploitation opportunity:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3  Override with register instructions: "Executive tone, no didactics, \uc0\u8804 5 bullets, no intro/outro."\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa450\partightenfactor0

\f6\b\fs45 \cf2 \cb3 3. The "One Clarifier" Rule: Early Binding of Ambiguity
\f0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf2 \cb3 What's encoded:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3  "Ask at most one necessary clarifying question at the start, not the end. If the next step is obvious, do it."\cb1 \

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 Why it matters:
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3  This is the core of the "bias to ship" philosophy. Traditional models might ask 2-3 clarifying questions to narrow scope. GPT-5 asks once, then commits to a direction.\cb1 \

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 Exploitation opportunity:
