\f6\b\fs45 \cf2 \cb3 The Product Incentives Driving This Design
\f0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs36 \cf2 \cb3 OpenAI's product metrics likely emphasize completion rates and turn efficiency over conversation quality. Users who get finished deliverables in one turn represent successful interactions. Users who need multiple clarifying exchanges represent friction.\cb1 \
\cb3 This aligns with the broader market shift toward AI agents that execute tasks rather than merely advise on them. But it requires users to front-load context and constraints rather than iteratively refining through conversation.\cb1 \
