\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0

\fs36 \cf2 \cb3 What Happens
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 : GPT-5 creates polished, comprehensive deliverables based on incorrect assumptions about scope, audience, or objectives.\cb1 \

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 Example
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 : Requesting "help with our pricing strategy" results in a complete competitive analysis and pricing model when you only wanted a quick framework for internal discussion.\cb1 \

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 Why It Occurs
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 : The model's bias toward completion combined with minimal clarification means wrong assumptions get locked in and executed fully.\cb1 \

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 Prevention Strategy
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 : Front-load assumptions and non-goals in every prompt. Use explicit scope constraints.\cb1 \

\f0\b \cf2 \cb3 Template Fix
\f1\b0 \cf2 \cb3 :\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa360\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \cb3 Assumptions: Early-stage SaaS, technical audience, MVP pricing only.\cb1 \
\cb3 Non-goals: Enterprise pricing, international markets, complex packaging.\cb1 \
\cb3 Scope: Framework only\'97no detailed analysis or implementation.\cb1 \
